    {
      "label": "In-context RL can handle variable action spaces and stitch skills.",
      "node_id": "claim:C0a",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Exploration can collapse; sparse reward and repetitive trajectories remain open (Section 4.6).",
      "node_id": "claim:C0b",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "How can exploration be governed without replacing the policy?",
      "node_id": "claim:C0c",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "A read-only governance layer reduces redundant search on a synthetic corpus.",
      "node_id": "claim:C1a",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "A generator/governor split increases distinct-state coverage versus a single explorer.",
      "node_id": "claim:C1b",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Results are limited to synthetic fixtures.",
      "node_id": "claim:C1c",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Does the effect hold under a trained policy?",
      "node_id": "claim:C1d",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "All reported numbers are replay-exact.",
      "node_id": "claim:C1e",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Separating generation and governance preserves exploration diversity on synthetic runs.",
      "node_id": "claim:C2a",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Soft re-weighting bounds accumulated authority drift.",
      "node_id": "claim:C2b",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Agents are rule-based stand-ins, not trained.",
      "node_id": "claim:C2c",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "How does the split scale to many agents?",
      "node_id": "claim:C2d",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Containment caps high-certainty incoherent paths on synthetic fixtures.",
      "node_id": "claim:C3a",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Containment may generalise beyond the fixtures.",
      "node_id": "claim:C3b",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Only a synthetic generator is evaluated.",
      "node_id": "claim:C3c",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "How does containment behave with a real generator?",
      "node_id": "claim:C3d",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Structural classification explains soft re-weighting decisions.",
      "node_id": "claim:C4a",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "The account is post-hoc, not causal.",
      "node_id": "claim:C4b",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Can governance be interpreted causally?",
      "node_id": "claim:C4c",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Read-only constraints avoid hidden optimisation authority.",
      "node_id": "claim:C5a",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Non-authoritative layers may reduce misalignment pressure.",
      "node_id": "claim:C5b",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "No real-world deployment is evaluated.",
      "node_id": "claim:C5c",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "How do constraints behave under distribution shift?",
      "node_id": "claim:C5d",
      "node_type": "Claim"
    },
    {
      "label": "Exploration benchmarks are replay-exact under fixed fixtures.",
